WEBVTT



00:00:10.016 --> 00:00:13.248
Welcome to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast.

00:00:13.376 --> 00:00:17.472
Our mission is to develop fully devoted followers of Christ.

00:00:17.920 --> 00:00:26.496
Welcome back to the podcast. on today's episode, we are concluding our journey through the book of Psalms with Pastor Matt, reading Psalm One fifty.

00:00:29.920 --> 00:00:35.488
Hello canopy roads welcome to day 166 in the psalms project

00:00:35.200 --> 00:00:45.184
we have made it all the way from psalms one to psalms one fifty. i'll tell you i have looked forward every morning to getting the notice on my app.

00:00:45.024 --> 00:00:55.072
that it's ready it's time for a Psalms project video and I have enjoyed all of your videos thank you all of you who participated in reading a Psalm and

00:00:54.592 --> 00:00:58.624
and recording it. I know for some of you that was terrifying.

00:00:58.368 --> 00:00:59.904
But you did it.

00:00:59.744 --> 00:01:07.744
so thank you for being a part of this amazing project this journey through the psalms i hope that it has blessed you as it's blessed me

00:01:07.520 --> 00:01:17.568
Just spending time in the psalms, so much time in the psalms has been a wonderful encouragement to me. And as I have preached through the Psalms, I have learned a whole lot

00:01:17.088 --> 00:01:27.136
whole lot that I didn't know about the Psalms. I hope that you have too, as you have read on your own and participated in the worship services as well. So we finally made it.

00:01:26.656 --> 00:01:32.960
We made it to Psalm 150 and how appropriate that this Psalm is about praise. Praise.

00:01:33.184 --> 00:01:35.456
in fact in six verses

00:01:35.488 --> 00:01:39.840
We are commanded 13 times to praise God.

00:01:41.024 --> 00:01:43.360
Psalm 150, 1-6.

00:01:43.328 --> 00:01:44.608
Praise the Lord.

00:01:44.576 --> 00:01:46.880
Praise God in His sanctuary.

00:01:46.560 --> 00:01:48.768
Praise Him in His mighty heavens.

00:01:48.448 --> 00:01:50.752
Praise Him for His mighty deeds.

00:01:50.688 --> 00:01:53.344
Praise Him according to His excellent greatness.

00:01:53.312 --> 00:01:57.056
Praise Him with trumpet sound. Praise Him with lute and harp.

00:01:57.024 --> 00:01:59.264
Praise him with tambourine and dance.

00:01:59.136 --> 00:02:01.184
Praise Him with strings and pipe.

00:02:01.280 --> 00:02:03.360
Praise Him with sounding cymbals.

00:02:03.328 --> 00:02:06.016
Praise him with loud clashing cymbals.

00:02:06.208 --> 00:02:08.960
Let everything that has breath

00:02:08.768 --> 00:02:10.144
Praise the Lord.

00:02:09.952 --> 00:02:12.736
Praise the Lord. That last verse is for us.

00:02:12.928 --> 00:02:15.232
Everything that has breath

00:02:15.360 --> 00:02:16.896
should praise God.

00:02:17.504 --> 00:02:22.656
He says, praise God in his sanctuary, and today I'm in our worship center.

00:02:22.528 --> 00:02:25.024
Which by the way is a paid off

00:02:24.864 --> 00:02:26.176
worship center.

00:02:26.624 --> 00:02:28.736
You found out on Christmas Eve

00:02:28.736 --> 00:02:34.432
that we paid off all of our debt so we praise God for his faithfulness to us

00:02:34.304 --> 00:02:42.112
over the last three years to be able to pay off this debt. So we praise God in this sanctuary for his mighty acts.

00:02:42.144 --> 00:02:46.816
It also says, "Praise God in His mighty heavens." That means, "Praise God outside."

00:02:46.688 --> 00:02:49.792
Some of my best praise times are outside.

00:02:49.760 --> 00:02:53.344
So I don't know where you're most inspired by God's greatness.

00:02:53.344 --> 00:02:56.160
But I'd encourage you today to find that place.

00:02:56.448 --> 00:02:58.592
Maybe it's your sanctuary.

00:02:58.688 --> 00:03:02.432
Maybe it's your lazy boy. Maybe it's your porch chair.

00:03:02.176 --> 00:03:04.864
uh maybe it's the outside taking a walk

00:03:05.952 --> 00:03:10.688
Find a time today to praise God. It says, "Praise God for His mighty deeds."

00:03:11.392 --> 00:03:13.088
There's no shortage of that.

00:03:13.248 --> 00:03:18.912
And praise God for his excellent greatness. Praise God for his almighty power.

00:03:19.392 --> 00:03:21.984
His ever presence in your life

00:03:22.048 --> 00:03:25.280
Praise God for His unlimited knowledge and wisdom.

00:03:25.216 --> 00:03:28.128
Praise God for His blameless character.

00:03:28.192 --> 00:03:36.032
Praise God for his love that is steadfast and pure. The word steadfast love appears again and again throughout the Psalms.

00:03:35.808 --> 00:03:39.296
He always loves you. Praise God for His mercy.

00:03:39.104 --> 00:03:41.504
Praise God for His righteousness.

00:03:41.344 --> 00:03:44.832
Praise God that He's eternal. Praise God that He's changeless.

00:03:45.216 --> 00:03:49.760
You'll never wake up and find God to be different one day than he was the next.

00:03:49.664 --> 00:03:51.072
Isn't that amazing?

00:03:51.808 --> 00:03:54.912
The all-loving, all-powerful God loves you.

00:03:55.584 --> 00:03:57.056
So we should praise him.

00:03:57.216 --> 00:04:01.504
I hope that you will spend your day or start your day and maybe spend your day

00:04:01.312 --> 00:04:02.592
Praising God.

00:04:02.560 --> 00:04:05.888
Praising God does such a wonderful thing for all of us.

00:04:06.304 --> 00:04:07.904
It puts life

00:04:08.032 --> 00:04:10.784
In all of its problems, the pandemic,

00:04:11.424 --> 00:04:14.848
Pains that we might have, challenges that we have.

00:04:14.624 --> 00:04:16.832
Losses that we've had this year.

00:04:17.216 --> 00:04:19.264
it puts all that in perspective.

00:04:19.488 --> 00:04:21.920
It reminds us that He's God.

00:04:22.208 --> 00:04:23.680
so we don't have to be.

00:04:25.024 --> 00:04:26.656
He's God and I'm not.

00:04:27.200 --> 00:04:29.344
That's a great way to begin the day.

00:04:29.568 --> 00:04:30.816
God bless you.

00:04:30.880 --> 00:04:32.544
Have a great day.

00:04:32.576 --> 00:04:34.784
living for and praising God.

00:04:43.968 --> 00:04:52.096
We hope this message was encouraging to you. If you would like this kind of content delivered directly to you, consider subscribing to our channel.

00:04:52.192 --> 00:05:01.664
If you'd like more information about our church, please visit us on the web at canopyroads.org. And thanks for listening to the Canopy Roads Baptist Church podcast.
